			<p>
				Welcome to your comprehensive guide for Achilles tendon rupture recovery. Whether you've recently
				experienced an injury or are in the midst of rehabilitation, we're here to help you understand
				the recovery process and guide you back to full health.
			</p>
			<p>
				An Achilles tendon rupture can be a challenging injury, but with proper care, patience, and
				dedication to rehabilitation, most patients can return to their normal activities. Recovery
				typically spans several months and involves multiple phases.
			</p>
			<p>Here are the key aspects of Achilles tendon rupture recovery:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Initial Treatment (0-2 weeks):</strong> Rest, immobilization, and pain management
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Early Recovery (2-6 weeks):</strong> Protected weight-bearing and gentle exercises
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Progressive Loading (6-12 weeks):</strong> Increased mobility and strengthening
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Return to Activity (3-6 months):</strong> Sport-specific training and conditioning
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Long-term Recovery:</strong> Ongoing maintenance and injury prevention
				</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Throughout this website, you'll find detailed information about each recovery phase, exercises,
				and tips for successful rehabilitation. Remember to always follow your healthcare provider's
				specific instructions, as recovery plans may vary based on individual circumstances.
			</p>
